@flexiarg vsatlatarium/sky-disk-continuum
@title Sky-Disk Continuum (Immersion ↔ Overview)
@audience interaction designers, digital library architects
@tone analytic
@style design-pattern
@sigils [🔭/盘]
@references [vsatlatarium/dome-projection vsatlas/interpretive-views]

! conclusion:
  Allow continuous zoom from immersive dome interior to external sky-disk
  overview so viewers can shift between situated reading and structural
  comprehension without changing mode.

  + context: You are designing navigation that spans close-reading and bird's-eye analysis within a single interaction. This does not apply when the corpus has no spatial projection (e.g., pure list views).
  + IF:
    Viewers need to alternate between exploring a neighbourhood of stories
    and surveying the whole constellation.

  + HOWEVER:
    Discrete mode switches (planetarium button vs geomview button) break
    flow and lose spatial orientation.

  + THEN:
    Let scroll-back move the camera past the dome origin so the
    surrounding sphere contracts into a visible disk. As the camera
    retreats, dome-projected arcs smoothly straighten to their natural
    bezier paths via debounced redraw at blended dome radius.

  + BECAUSE:
    Continuous zoom preserves the viewer's mental model of where they are
    in the constellation. The transition from "inside looking out" to
    "outside looking in" is a zoom, not a teleport.

  + STATUS:
    status[ready]
    evidence[VSATLATARIUM scroll-back with arc redraw — quantised blend, 20 steps]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Animate node positions to match arc straightening (currently nodes stay dome-projected).]
    next[Test whether the sky-disk view is useful for facilitators projecting to a group.]
    next[Explore whether the continuum works in VR (headset zoom via thumbstick push/pull).]
